HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 977
By Hicks T
A RESOLUTION to confirm the appointment of Steven Emil
Johnson to the Tennessee Fish and Wildlife
Commission.
WHEREAS, Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 70-1-201, provides for the creation of
the Tennessee Fish and Wildlife Commission; and
WHEREAS, Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 70-1-201(a), further provides that the
Speaker of the House of Representatives shall appoint two (2) members to the commission; and
WHEREAS, the Honorable Cameron Sexton, Speaker of the House of Representatives,
has appointed Steven Emil Johnson of Bristol to serve on the Tennessee Fish and Wildlife
Commission; and
WHEREAS, subject to confirmation, Mr. Johnson will serve a term on the commission
that expires on February 28, 2029; and
WHEREAS, a native of Huntsville, Alabama, Steve Johnson is the president of Johnson
Commercial Development, a full-service real estate development and management company
that is one of the leading and most experienced real estate companies in the Southeastern
United States; and
WHEREAS, in 1988, Mr. Johnson graduated from Virginia Tech, where he was a
standout tight end for the Hokies; following his college career, he played for the New England
Patriots before embarking on his career in commercial development; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Johnson is an outdoorsman who is well informed on the subject of the
conservation of game animals, birds, and fish in the State; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Johnson's experience and dedication to wildlife and conservation issues
would be a tremendous asset to the Tennessee Fish and Wildlife Commission; and
HJR0977
013012
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 70-1-201(b)(1), provides that the
members appointed to the Tennessee Fish and Wildlife Commission by the Speaker of the
House of Representatives shall be confirmed by the Senate Energy, Agriculture and Natural
Resources Committee and the appropriate committee of the House of Representatives and by
joint resolution of the General Assembly; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we hereby confirm the appointment of Steven Emil Johnson to a term on
the Tennessee Fish and Wildlife Commission, such term to expire on February 28, 2029.
